The following policy is an addition to the Exam and Coursework
Regulations and Procedures as outlined in the NAIT
Electronics/Computer Engineering Handbook.  {\em It is the student's
  responsibility to be aware of the information contained in the
  handbook in addition to the following policy.}

{\bf Use of Electronic Devices During Exams}

No electronic devices other that the approved calculator as outlined
in the appropriate student guide, or necessary medical devices, will
be allowed in an examination room during exams.  The use of a
calculator will be permitted only in exams were such use is considered
appropriate to the content of the exam, and such use is specifically
permitted by the examiner.  For the purpose of this policy, exams are
defined as any measurement tool used to determine learning taking place
in classrooms, labs or in the field.  These include but are not
limietd to lab exams, quizzes, midterm exams, final exams, etc.

{\em Definition of electronic devices: Including but not limited to
  personal stereos, MP3 players, PDA's, cellular phones, radios,
  electronic daytimers, handhelp computers, and laptops.}

The examination envigilator will ensure proper implementation of this
policy and any decisions will be final.  Any challenges to an
envigilators decision must be made in writion to an Assistant Program
Head of the appropriate program. 
